/health/nodes get

get

List all nodes health

get /health/nodes

List all nodes health

Secured by itsyouonline with scopes:
  • user:memberof:0-orchestrator

OAuth2 is a protocol that lets external apps request authorization to private details in a user's account without getting their password.

  • Response
  • Security

HTTP status code 200

Body

Media type: application/json

Type: array of NodeHealthCheck

Items: NodeHealthCheck

  • id: required (string)
  • status: required (string)

    Status will be OK unless one of the healthchecks has a status WARNING or ERROR. If all healthchecks have a status SKIPPED, then status will be SKIPPED.

  • hostname: required (string)

Secured by itsyouonline

Headers

  • Authorization: required (string)

    Used to send a valid OAuth 2 access token. Do not use together with the "access_token" query string parameter.

Query Parameters

  • access_token: required (string)

    Used to send a valid OAuth 2 access token. Do not use together with the "Authorization" header

/nodes/{nodeid}/jobs/{jobid} get delete

get

Get the details of a submitted job

delete

Kills the job

get /nodes/{nodeid}/jobs/{jobid}

Get the details of a submitted job

Secured by itsyouonline with scopes:
  • user:memberof:0-orchestrator

OAuth2 is a protocol that lets external apps request authorization to private details in a user's account without getting their password.

  • Request
  • Response
  • Security

URI Parameters

  • nodeid: required (string)
  • jobid: required (string)

Annotations

  • DirectAccess

HTTP status code 200

Body

Media type: application/json

Type: object

Properties
  • id: required (string)

    The unique identifier for the job

  • name: required (one of core.ping, core.system, core.kill, core.killall, core.state, core.reboot, info.cpu, info.disk, info.mem, info.nic, info.os, container.create, container.list, container.dispatch, container.terminate, bridge.create, bridge.list, bridge.delete, disk.list, disk.mktable, disk.mkpart, disk.rmpart, disk.mount, disk.umount, btrfs.create, btrfs.list, btrfs.subvol_create, btrfs.subvol_list, btrfs.subvol_delete)

    The kind of job to which this result belongs to.

  • level: required (integer)

    20 means that the data is json serialized object

  • startTime: required (number)

    Epoch timestamp when the job was started

  • stdout: required (string)

    Stdout of process/job

  • stderr: required (string)

    Stderr of process/job

  • state: required (one of unknown_cmd, error, success, killed, timeout, duplicate_id, running)

    Status of the job

  • data: required (string)

    The result of executing the job

Secured by itsyouonline

Headers

  • Authorization: required (string)

    Used to send a valid OAuth 2 access token. Do not use together with the "access_token" query string parameter.

Query Parameters

  • access_token: required (string)

    Used to send a valid OAuth 2 access token. Do not use together with the "Authorization" header

HTTP status code 404

Annotations

  • AYSBased

Body

Media type: application/json

Type: object

Properties
  • name: required (string - maxLength: 15)

    Name for the bridge to be created. The name can't be "default".

  • hwaddr: (string)

    MAC address for the bridge to be created. If none, a random MAC address will be assigned.

  • networkMode: required (one of none, static, dnsmasq)

    Networking mode

  • nat: required (boolean)

    If true, SNAT will be enabled on this bridge.

  • setting: required (object)

    Networking settings are depending on the selected 'networkMode' as follows:

    • networkMode = 'none': No settings Bridge won't get any IP settings.
    • networkMode = 'static': settings={'cidr': 'ip/net'} Bridge will get assigned the given IP address.
    • networkMode= 'dnsmasq': settings={'cidr': 'ip/net', 'start': 'ip', 'end': 'ip'} Bridge will get assigned the IP address specified for 'cidr' and each running container that is attached to this IP address will get an IP address within the specified start/end range. Netmask of the range is the netmask part of the provided CIDR. If 'nat' is set to true, SNAT rules will be automatically added in the firewall.
    • cidr: required (string)
    • start: required (string)
    • end: required (string)

HTTP status code 202

Bridge created successfully

  • Location: required (string)

    URL to the created bridge resource

Body

Media type: application/json

Type: Run

HTTP status code 409

post /vdiskstorage/{vdiskstorageid}/vdisks

Create a new vdisk, can be a copy from an existing vdisk

Secured by itsyouonline with scopes:
  • user:memberof:0-orchestrator

OAuth2 is a protocol that lets external apps request authorization to private details in a user's account without getting their password.

  • Request
  • Response
  • Security

URI Parameters

  • vdiskstorageid: required (string)

Annotations

  • AYSBased

Body

Media type: application/json

Type: object

Properties
  • id: required (string)

    name of the vdisk. need to be unique

  • size: required (integer)

    Size of the vdisk in GiB

  • blocksize: required (integer - default: 4096)

    blocksize in bytes

  • type: required (one of boot, db, cache, tmp)
    • boot: A boot disk is a redundant disk that can be initialized based on a templatevdisk. See templatevdisk property. Boot disks should only be used for the operating system and applications installed on the operating system. Performance of bootdisks is not optimized because that defeats their purpose.
    • db: A db disk is a redundant disk optimized for performant block storage. DB disks should be used for running reliable high io intensive workloads such as databases, key value stores, ...
    • cache: A cache disk is a persistent non redundant disk optimized for performant block storage. Cache disks should be used for high io intensive workloads which don't need to be highly reliable.
    • tmp: A tmp disk is a non persistent non redundant disk optimized for performant block storage. Content in tmp disks is only available while mounted. Tmp disks should be used for swap and mounts in /tmp.
    disk type redundant persistent template support rollback performance optimized
    boot yes yes yes yes no
    db yes yes no yes yes
    cache no yes no no yes
    tmp no no no no yes
